d\theta = \frac{1}{r^2} \left( x\;dy - y\;dx \right)\quad\text{where }r^2 = x^2 + y^2
x=r\cos\theta
y=r\sin\theta
\theta
\frac{\text{d}x}{\text{d}\theta}
y
\frac{\text{d}y}{\text{d}\theta}
x
\text{d}\theta
\frac{\text{d}x}{\text{d}\theta}=-r\sin\theta=-y
y\frac{\text{d}x}{\text{d}\theta}=-y^2
\frac{\text{d}y}{\text{d}\theta}=r\cos\theta=x
x\frac{\text{d}y}{\text{d}\theta}=x^2
(x\text{d}y-y\text{d}x)/\text{d}\theta=r^2
x\left(\frac{\text{d}y}{\text{d}\theta}\right)-y\left(\frac{\text{d}x}{\text{d}\theta}\right)=x^2+y^2=r^2.
x\frac{\text{d}y}{\text{d}\theta}-y\frac{\text{d}x}{\text{d}\theta}=x^2+y^2=r^2.
